<br>
Nearly falling over with laughter, Kimaya sped around the corner to hide from the merchant who had just angrily found that all of his displays had been carefully arranged so that the suits of fine armor appeared to be doing unnatural things to one another.  She simply loved Shadowhaven, there was a whole city full of people who had never before enjoyed a good pixie prank!<br>
<br>
One of the suits of armor glinted again in her mind, and she might have wanted to take it if she didn't think it would be wrong.  She was thinking of how good it would have looked on her secret lover, the one she met by chance once before, then again by design and secrecy a couple times after.  She still found herself mildly saddened by the almost-fight they had a while before, moreso now that she had an idea of how it had happened.  Was he drawn into a web of suspicion, or simply of jealousy?<br>
<br>
Sighing, she tossed the whole question aside.  All she knew was that she had told him the truth, that she’d never do anything that would hurt him, and she tried again to suppress a fresh wave of hurt that he'd ever have such a fear.  She had even shared a secret part of herself to hopefully reassure him, but she knew his path wasn’t her decision to make…  <br>
<br>
Soon her ponderings were interrupted, for she heard a little pixie whisper that her secret sweetheart was nearby.  Her mind slipped him a message that she wanted to see him again, then laughed back at his surprise.  She tried to explain that she wasn't angry anymore, she only wanted to see him again, and she STILL wanted to despite the dangers they both may have faced.  Finally, when she agreed to his request that she wear her blood-red leathers, he said he could no longer resist her invitation.<br>
<br>
After careful arrangements and hurried sneaking around corners, she led him into a seldom-visited bar.  She purchased a rare champagne to celebrate another of their equally rare visits, but he insisted he found her beauty more intoxicating.  She only laughed, then suggested with a wink that perhaps he should see her in her blue wicker just to see if he liked that better.  He reluctantly agreed, almost certain he'd like nothing more than how she then looked.  <br>
<br>
Though she was half-suspicious he agreed solely so he could catch glimpses of her changing, his eyes lit up as she came out in the tight dark-violet leathers, her curves faintly visible through thin gauze.  She giggled as she saw his eyes wander where his hands wanted to, as almost everyone ended up voting for the violet...<br>
<br>
After a quick slap on his hand and a reminder that the bank was not a place to test the texture, she led him back to the bar in hopes he'd take more champagne.  Yet he said all he wished for was a taste of was her lips, and of her soft creamy neck that he whispered he had longed for so long... when he suddenly remembered they were still in a public place, however semi-private.  Instead he slipped behind her to hold her in his lap while they talked of... what had they spoken of?  It hardly mattered, as before long his hands spoke of a desire for a more private place, and her voice suggested they find one.<br>
<br>
There was in inn nearby, with one empty room.  It was a small room with an even smaller bed.  There were few words spoken before he lifted her up onto the bed, his eyes meeting hers with a quiet intensity.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> He asks softly, 'Kimaya, may I please make love to you this night?'<br>
Kimaya laughs, 'Why only tonight?  What's wrong with tomorrow and the next night as well?'  Softening her mirth into a faint smile, she replies again, 'Yes, please, I've been waiting for you to ask.'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
With hardly a hint of shyness, he asked her for help with his armor, then helped her shed hers.  The shyness surfaced soon enough, however, as he admitted, or half-asked another question.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> His words were softly spoken, 'This is my first time.  Is that okay?'<br>
She doesn't reply with laughter, but gives him a sweet smile and a sparkle in her eyes. 'Of course it's okay, sweetheart.'<br>
He smiles back, his eyes still looking into hers.  'I'm so glad it's with you.'<br>
She pulls him closer, whispering, 'I can't find the words tell you how much it means that it's with me, too.'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
With a faint rustle of sheets, he snuffed out the candles and slipped gently into the welcoming darkness.<br>
