<br>
He wanted to get to Luclin, but since she didn't yet know how to bring him directly there she offered to bring him to Toxxulia Forest instead.  And as soon as he said he'd never been to one of her most favoritest woods, she started casting the spell to change that sad oversight.  He seemed to find the woods interesting, but he swore the only sight he wished  to see was her.  She giggled, blushed and smooched him again before tugging at him to follow her.  She didn’t want to be late.<br>
<br>
She wished she had time to show him all the places she loved around there, but she knew it wasn't the right time anyways.  Some sharings were for some people at some times, while other things were right for others.  So instead she camouflaged him and slipped herself back out of view, trying not to let themselves be seen together lest they get teased, or worse.  Even so, she couldn't keep herself from a sneaking pinch or a stolen kiss now and then while they waited for the spires.<br>
<br>
When they reached Luclin, they knew they couldn't part right away.  They continued sneaking through Shadowhaven, moving carefully with her scouting ahead to ensure none of his companions would spot them together.  If there was one thing Kimayas were good at, it was being sneaky and remaining unseen, especially when it would help keep a loved one out of mischief.<br>
<br>
Finally, they had made it to her room, not even pausing for drinks or any other pretense of how they wished to share their precious time together.  Casual conversation, shyness, clothing... all were carelessly tossed aside in the comfortable joy they had always shared with one another.  <br>
<br>
He had backed her into a corner soon enough, yet rather than feeling trapped she felt safe and close, though still somehow coy and bashful as she often was with him.  Was it his boyish enthusiasm, his shy politeness... could she ever be sure?  Ignorant of the reasons he had such an effect on her, she still giggled freely and shivered softly as his gentle hands and soft lips caressed and tickled her skin.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> He asks, 'My lady, may I please make love to you?  A gentleman always asks.'<br>
Kimaya giggles, smiling with sweet, bright eyes as she replies, 'And a Kimaya who loves you always says yes.'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
He carried her quietly to the bed, the time they shared even sweeter than the time before, and their eyes locked into one another's through each moment they were not closed in happiness.  After a shared eternity of blissful moments, he pulled her close to sit in his lap and gently patted her belly.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> He whispers into her ear, 'We'll have to be careful.  You know, babies can grow in there.'<br>
Kimaya laughs, putting her hand over his and holding it tightly against her.  'Oh, silly, I'm not gonna have a BABY!  There's fae secrets, and they make sure there's no babies until it's time.'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
She nodded emphatically, secure in her belief it wouldn't be time for quite a while, maybe even never.  He still held her close, and mused aloud about what his companions would say if they knew she was carrying his child.  She laughed and joked that it would be the same thing they'd say if it were a Tuesday, though she was half-aware he didn’t find the whole topic quite so funny.<br>
<br>
Soon it was time for them to part again -- he had another hunt to join and she had another errand to run or crisis to help with.  They shared one lingering kiss and went their separate ways, once more shifting from secret lovers to cherished memories. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=416.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=416.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=416.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.threadControl?topicID=416.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=416.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=416.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option value="firionaviefrm58">Telegrams!<option value="firionaviefrm47">Guilds and Associations<option value="fi